author_ssm: Mary Allison Farley, Erika Gottfried, and Rachel Searcy
abstract_ssm: Samuel Zagat was a Lithuanian-Jewish artist best known for his work as a cartoonist, first for his popular comic strip Gimpel Beinish" and later for his political cartoons.  This collection documents Zagat's career as a cartoonist and more generally illustrates the efforts of an American cartoonist working in Yiddish.  Materials include photographs, original drawings, negatives, contact prints, and newspaper clippings.  Major subjects include labor relations, anti-Semitism, Cold War diplomacy, Israel and the Middle East, and humorous aspects of daily Jewish life.
